[{"id":"FT537470","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n<img alt=\"An equilateral soil triangle is shown with sand at the lower left vertex, silt at the lower right vertex, and clay at the top vertex. Along the bottom edge the sand percent increases from right to left from 0 percent to 100 percent. Along the left leg the clay percent increases from 0 percent at the lower left vertex to 100 percent at the top vertex. Along the right leg the silt percent increases from 0 percent at the top vertex to 100 percent at the lower right vertex. Letters indicate locations along the inner edge of the triangle. Point A is just inside the lower left vertex. Point B is halfway up the left leg. Point C is just below the top vertex. Point D is halfway down the right leg. Point E is just inside the lower right vertex. \" height=\"424\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/0dbc71b61291b41d44f577a4424b37fe/original.png\" width=\"460\">\n<p>Which soil indicated on the soil triangle above would most likely have the highest water-holding capacity?</p>","choicesHtml":["<p>Soil A</p>","<p>Soil B</p>","<p>Soil C</p>","<p>Soil D</p>","<p>Soil E</p>"],"answer":1}]